  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Food Security</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will promote agroecological food production on 200 small family farms (quintais) in the municipalities of Remanso (semi-arid) and Camamu (Atlantic forest). Participants will learn to diversify their farms with vegetable, fruit, timber, forage and medicinal species, as well as small animal husbandry (120 goats, 6,000 fish and 4,800 chickens), favoring a process of agroecological innovation. The project will reach a total of 500 families through resource-sharing (revolving fund), passing on the gift and agroecological capacity-building among farmers. The aim is to enhance the supply of food and medicinal plants for families in eight communities near Sobradinho and Baixo Sul, Bahia State. The project will also systematize agroecological farming in those communities, improve food security and serve as the basis for broader public policy to support family agriculture.</narrative>
  </description>
